{
  "name": "Inescapable Lash*",
  "type": "weapon",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The lash is very tightly braided bronze colored leather with a leather-wrapped handle.<span style=\"font-size:10.5px\"> </span>It is extremely long, whirls up easily, and stretches quite a distance before it snaps. As it has awoken it ripples with pink energy.</p><p>The whip is a magical weapon with a 15-foot reach. It deals slashing damage based on how close they are to you.</p><ul><li>Within 5 feet = 3d4 slashing damage</li><li>10 feet = 2d4 slashing damage</li><li>15 feet = 1d4 slashing damage</li></ul><p>If it hits a large or smaller creature, the attuned can choose to either <strong>grapple</strong> the target, which also becomes <strong>restrained</strong>, or to pull the target 15 feet towards them. The target can make a Strength saving throw (DC = 8 + proficiency bonus + your choice of Strength or Dexterity) to attempt to escape the <strong>grapple</strong> at the end of their turn. It can also be used to <strong>grapple</strong> objects. Any <strong>grapple</strong> caused by the lash immediately ends should the wielder drop the whip.</p><p>The whip can only have one creature or object <strong>grappled</strong> at a time. While the whip has a creature or object <strong>grappled</strong>, it cannot be used to make attacks.</p><p>At any time while you have a creature <strong>grappled</strong> and would take damage, you can use your <strong>reaction</strong> to reduce the damage you would take by half. The <strong>grappled</strong> creature then makes a Charisma saving throw (DC = 8 + proficiency bonus + your choice of Strength or Dexterity), and on a failed save they take the other half of the damage. On a success they take no damage.</p><blockquote><p><strong>If you wish to make the save DC against being grappled use Strength instead of Dexterity, edit the Details section and change the \"vs. DC\" drop-down to Strength.</strong></p></blockquote>",
      "chat": ""
    },
